Sentencas: A comprehensive three-dimensional model for an assembled button solid oxide fuel cell is developed by coupling thermal-electrochemical and mechanical models.
Titulo: Thermo-Electro-Chemo-Mechanical Modeling of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell for Stress and Failure Evolution during Duty Cycle

Sentencas: Different mechanical effects including residual strain, thermal strain, accelerated and normal creep, mechanical properties change of anode, as well as chemical expansion are considered.
Titulo: Thermo-Electro-Chemo-Mechanical Modeling of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell for Stress and Failure Evolution during Duty Cycle

Sentencas: The mechanical response of the button cell subjected to an idealized duty cycle from the as-fabricated state, heating-up stage, reduction stage, to three operation periods of 800 degrees C, 700 degrees C, and 600 degrees C is numerically simulated.
Titulo: Thermo-Electro-Chemo-Mechanical Modeling of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell for Stress and Failure Evolution during Duty Cycle

Sentencas: Simulations are based on and validated by the experimental polarization curves and residual stress curve.
Titulo: Thermo-Electro-Chemo-Mechanical Modeling of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell for Stress and Failure Evolution during Duty Cycle

Sentencas: Results show that the sealant is susceptible to fracture at the as-fabricated state, while the cathode is likely to fail during heating-up stage.
Titulo: Thermo-Electro-Chemo-Mechanical Modeling of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell for Stress and Failure Evolution during Duty Cycle

Sentencas: The accelerated creep effect during reduction significantly eliminates the tensile stress in the anode nevertheless leads to higher stress in the cathode and electrolyte.
Titulo: Thermo-Electro-Chemo-Mechanical Modeling of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell for Stress and Failure Evolution during Duty Cycle

Sentencas: It indicates that the assumption of zero-stress temperature at the reduction point could cause an underestimation of stress in the cathode and electrolyte in the case of a constrained cell.
Titulo: Thermo-Electro-Chemo-Mechanical Modeling of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell for Stress and Failure Evolution during Duty Cycle

Sentencas: The chemical expansion effect in the cathode is more prominent at higher operating temperatures.
Titulo: Thermo-Electro-Chemo-Mechanical Modeling of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell for Stress and Failure Evolution during Duty Cycle

Sentencas: A minimum failure probability of the cell is found at 700 degrees C with consideration of chemical expansion.
Titulo: Thermo-Electro-Chemo-Mechanical Modeling of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell for Stress and Failure Evolution during Duty Cycle
